  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Contingency Fund - World Health Organization (WHO) 2015</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="FR">Fonds de r&#xE9;serve - Organisation mondiale de la sant&#xE9; (OMS) 2015</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="FR">L&#x2019;&#xE9;closion du virus &#xC9;bola en Afrique de l&#x2019;Ouest a mis en lumi&#xE8;re l&#x2019;importance de r&#xE9;pondre rapidement et efficacement &#xE0; l&#x2019;&#xE9;closion de maladies, ce afin d&#x2019;en limiter la propagation et d&#x2019;en att&#xE9;nuer les r&#xE9;percussions. L&#x2019;Organisation mondiale de la sant&#xE9; (OMS) a donc cr&#xE9;&#xE9; un fonds de r&#xE9;serve pour permettre un acc&#xE8;s rapide et souple au financement visant &#xE0; soutenir les &#xE9;tapes imm&#xE9;diates de ses interventions aux &#xE9;ventuelles &#xE9;closions, notamment lorsqu&#x2019;il est question d&#x2019;une urgence de sant&#xE9; publique de port&#xE9;e internationale. Le financement comble le manque &#xE0; gagner entre le d&#xE9;but d&#x2019;une situation d&#x2019;urgence et le moment o&#xF9; les appels de l&#x2019;OMS permettent de r&#xE9;unir suffisamment de fonds. L&#x2019;objectif est de recueillir 100 millions $ pour le fonds de r&#xE9;serve.  Gr&#xE2;ce au soutien que le MAECD fournit au fonds de r&#xE9;serve, l&#x2019;OMS est mieux en mesure d&#x2019;intervenir lors d&#x2019;&#xE9;ventuelles &#xE9;closions de maladies.</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The West African Ebola outbreak has underlined the importance of a timely and effective response to disease outbreaks in order to contain their spread and mitigate their impact. In response, the World Health Organization (WHO) has established the WHO Contingency Fund. The Fund is designed to provide rapid access to flexible funding to support the immediate stages of its response to future outbreaks, particularly those declared a Public Health Emergency of International Concern. The Fund bridges the gap between the start of an emergency and the point at which the WHO has raised adequate resources through its funding appeals. The total target size of the Contingency Fund is $100 million.  With DFATD&#x2019;s support, the WHO is better prepared to respond to future disease outbreaks.</narrative>
  </description>
